Sentencas: Symmetric electrodes are critical for lowering manufacturing costs and commercializing solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) technology.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: SrFeO3-derived electrode materials demonstrated considerable potential for symmetrical SOFCs.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The present work comprehensively investigates the electrochemical performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-delta as symmetric electrodes.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The powder is synthesized using the solid-state reaction method.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Despite stabilizing the cubic perovskite phase, a significant oxygen deficiency within the lattice is determined.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Upon testing the symmetrical half-cells at 800 degrees C, SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-delta offers an extremely low initial area specific resistance (ASR) of 0.03 Omegacm(2) in O-2 and 0.067 Omegacm(2) in 3%H2O/H-2.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Although the ASR remains unchanged in O-2, it increases to 0.24 Omegacm(2) in 3%H2O/H-2 after 100 h of thermal aging.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Similar behavior is seen on redox cycling the half-cells.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The ASR increase in reducing conditions is attributed to the microcracks generation.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrolyte-supported symmetrical single cells deliver a maximum power density of 509 mWcm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This value declines to 409 mWcm(-2) on thermal aging for 100 h. A power density loss similar to 449 mWcm(-2) is seen on performing multiple redox cycles (at the anode side) at 800 degrees C. Interestingly, a slight increase in electrode polarization resistance is recorded during these tests, highlighting the stability of the SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-delta electrode in the SOFC environment.
Titulo: Probing the Electrochemical Performance of SrFe0.9Ti0.1O3-δ for the Symmetric Electrode in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
